## Web Proxy for Vercel and Static Serverless Sites

This proxy is designed to handle requests to Vercel and static serverless sites. It can be used to modify or transform requests and responses, and to add additional functionality.

### Usage

To use the proxy, you will need to:

1. Deploy the proxy to a Vercel or other serverless platform.
2. Configure your client-side application to use the proxy as its base URL.
3. Make requests to the proxy as you would normally make requests to the target site.

### Features

The proxy includes the following features:

* Support for Vercel and static serverless sites
* Request and response modification
* Additional functionality, such as authentication and rate limiting

### Limitations

The proxy has the following limitations:

* It does not support all possible request and response types.
* It may not be compatible with all client-side applications.

### Documentation

For more information on how to use the proxy, please refer to the following documentation:

* [Deployment instructions](https://github.com/vercel/web-proxy-vercel/blob/main/docs/deployment.md)
* [Configuration instructions](https://github.com/vercel/web-proxy-vercel/blob/main/docs/configuration.md)
* [API reference](https://github.com/vercel/web-proxy-vercel/blob/main/docs/api.md)

### Contributing

Contributions to the proxy are welcome. Please read the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/vercel/web-proxy-vercel/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md) before submitting a pull request.

